# SLOP Styling

Use **CSS Modules** only. No Tailwind, styled-components, or global CSS for component styling (unless the plan is updated).

## Conventions

- **File naming**: One CSS Module per component (or per route/page) when needed. Name: `ComponentName.module.css` next to `ComponentName.tsx` (e.g. `ProductCard.module.css` next to `ProductCard.tsx`).
- **Import**: `import styles from './ComponentName.module.css'` and use `styles.className` in JSX. No global class names for component-specific styles.
- **Class names**: Use camelCase in the CSS file and reference as `styles.camelCase` (e.g. `.cardWrapper`, `.centralList`). Avoid BEM in the file unless the team prefers it; keep names short and semantic.
- **Scoping**: Classes in `.module.css` are locally scoped. Use them for layout, spacing, and visual state of that component. Shared tokens (e.g. colors, font sizes) can live in a shared module (e.g. `tokens.module.css` or `variables.module.css`) and be imported where needed.
- **No inline styles for layout** – Prefer classes in CSS Modules for layout and responsive behavior; reserve inline styles for one-off overrides or dynamic values (e.g. position from drag).

When adding new UI components, add a colocated `*.module.css` and use it instead of introducing a new styling system.
